  m_text: "The liquid stream collected from the separator consists of a crude mixture
    of methanol and water, which must be purified based on their differing boiling
    points. \n\nAs thermal energy vaporizes the liquid at the bottom, the rising
    vapor becomes highly enriched with methanol as it passes through internal fractionating
    trays, eventually condensing at the top to yield industrial-grade pure product
    while water is safely discharged from the bottom. "
