  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "The reactor outlet stream is a hot, high-pressure gas mixture containing
    methanol, water vapor, and unreacted gases such as CO2, CO, and H2. The condenser
    cools this stream rapidly using a cooling medium, causing methanol and water
    vapors to condense into liquid while lighter gases remain in the gas phase. \n\nThis
    phase change is driven purely by temperature reduction, no chemical reaction
    takes place inside the condenser.\n\nThe resulting two-phase mixture is then
    sent to the flash separator, where liquid and gas are physically separated. The
    gas phase, still rich in unreacted H2 and CO2, is partially recycled back to
    the reactor inlet to improve overall conversion efficiency and reduce feedstock
    waste."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
